<div id="review_2229807712" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2229807712" />
    <a title="Charlotte May" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14002983-charlotte-may"><img alt="Charlotte May" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641295530p2/14002983.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2229807712?book_show_action=true">Sep 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Charlotte May" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Charlotte May" href="/user/show/14002983-charlotte-may">Charlotte May</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780718187446" href="/book/show/37673923-the-chalk-man">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14002983-charlotte-may?shelf=crime-mystery-thriller">crime-mystery-thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2229807712" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16263181231066781681"><i> “The time for my childhood bogeyman has gone. I’m an adult now. Time to face the Chalk Man.” </i> <br/><br/>This was a creepy and gripping read. <br/><br/>It follows two timelines of the main character Eddie. The first is in 1986 when Eddie is 12. The second is present day and Eddie is middle aged. <br/><br/>When Eddie was young there was a local teacher who always hovered around and was pale as anything, nicknamed the Chalk Man. Meanwhile Eddie and his friends use chalk to draw stick men and leave messages for one another. <br/><br/>So </span>
  <span id="freeText16263181231066781681" style="display:none"><i> “The time for my childhood bogeyman has gone. I’m an adult now. Time to face the Chalk Man.” </i> <br /><br />This was a creepy and gripping read. <br /><br />It follows two timelines of the main character Eddie. The first is in 1986 when Eddie is 12. The second is present day and Eddie is middle aged. <br /><br />When Eddie was young there was a local teacher who always hovered around and was pale as anything, nicknamed the Chalk Man. Meanwhile Eddie and his friends use chalk to draw stick men and leave messages for one another. <br /><br />So when their chalk men inadvertently lead them to a dead girls body parts things get weird. Everyone thinks they know who is guilty, but 30 years down the track Eddie still isn’t sure. <br /><br />There are plenty of unanswered questions and I enjoyed how everything was tied up. A good thriller for me has to make sure it answers all its questions which this definitely did. <br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ the only thing I will say is that the reverend being the murderer wasn’t a massive shock. I mean if it wasn’t Mr Holloran who else would it be? But I liked that all his friends had secrets (Hoppo killed Mickey, Gav stole Sean’s bike which got him killed. I especially liked how it ended with Eddie showing the beginnings of dementia like his dad. Though the fact he kept a head in his house was mental.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />Overall as far as debuts go this was very impressive and I will be reading more by C J Tudor.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16263181231066781681" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


